# 🐄 Nipple-Troughs Calf Welfare Analysis
*Statistical Pipeline for Water Delivery Method Study*

---

## 📂 **SCRIPTS DIRECTORY STRUCTURE**
scripts/
├── 00_config.R          # 🏁 Bootstrap project
├── 01_data_cleaning.R   # 🧹 Data wrangling
├── 02_climate_analysis.R
├── 03_growth_analysis.R
├── 04_behavior_analysis.R
├── 05_water_analysis.R
├── 06_feed_analysis.R
├── 07_cross_sucking_analysis.R
└── 08_visualization.R   # 📊 Master plots
🔥 CORE FEATURES
00_config.R ⚙️
The project backbone
▸ Installs/Loads all packages
▸ Sets global options:

r
options(contrasts = c("contr.sum", "contr.poly"))  # Type III SS
▸ Custom ggplot theme:

r
theme_custom <- function() {
  theme_minimal(base_size = 12) +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) 
}
01_data_cleaning.R 🧼
Data standardization pipeline
✔ Filters excluded calves (ID: 1442, 35, 1449)
✔ Recodes treatments:

r
mutate(Treatment = recode(Treatment, 
                         "Bico" = "Nipple-WT",
                         "Controle" = "Open-WT"))
✔ Output: cleaned_data.rds

📈 ANALYSIS TEMPLATE
All analysis scripts (02-07) follow:

📋 Descriptive Stats

r
df %>% 
  group_by(Treatment) %>% 
  summarise(Mean = mean(Weight), 
            SD = sd(Weight),
            CV = (SD/Mean)*100)
🔍 Assumption Checks

r
# Normality
shapiro.test(df$Weight)
# Homogeneity
leveneTest(Weight ~ Treatment, data = df)
🤖 Modeling

r
lmer(Weight ~ Treatment + (1|id), data = df)
💾 Output
Saves to output/[analysis]_results.rds

🎨 08_visualization.R
Centralized plotting control

r
# Treatment effect plot
plot_treatment <- function(data) {
  ggplot(data, aes(Treatment, Weight)) + 
    geom_boxplot(aes(fill = Treatment)) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = treatment_palette)
}
🚀 QUICKSTART
r
# Run full pipeline
source("scripts/00_config.R")
source("scripts/01_data_cleaning.R")
source("scripts/03_growth_analysis.R")  # Example analysis

